  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nGradle build cache prevents source packages to be installed to local Maven repository\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`mvn install -Prelease` should install the source package to local Maven repository\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`mvn install -Prelease` gets the source package from the cache, puts to `target` but does not install it to local Maven repo.\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n```\r\nrm -r ~/.m2/repository/io/quarkus/resteasy/reactive/resteasy-reactive-vertx/999-SNAPSHOT\r\ncd quarkus\r\n\r\nmvn install -DskipTests -ntp -Prelease -f independent-projects/resteasy-reactive/server/vertx/pom.xml\r\n...\r\n[INFO] --- source:3.2.1:jar-no-fork (attach-sources) @ resteasy-reactive-vertx ---\r\n[INFO] Loaded from the build cache, saving 0.029s\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter that the source package is in target\r\n\r\n```\r\nls -l independent-projects/resteasy-reactive/server/vertx/target | grep sources.jar\r\n-rw-r--r--. 1 ppalaga ppalaga  21826 Mar 15 23:21 resteasy-reactive-vertx-999-SNAPSHOT-sources.jar\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut not in local Maven repo:\r\n\r\n```\r\nls -l ~/.m2/repository/io/quarkus/resteasy/reactive/resteasy-reactive-vertx/999-SNAPSHOT | grep sources.jar\r\n# no output\r\n```\r\n\r\nWorkaround: run the build with `-Dno-build-cache`.\r\n\r\n\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\nirrelevant \n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nirrelevant \n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\nirrelevant \n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\nirrelevant \n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
